cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CY 

This paper discusses the evaluation of neural models for historical text normalization, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also focuses on the generalization of these models to new datasets and languages, which suggests relevance to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the use of neural models implies a connection to sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper's emphasis on evaluation and comparison of different systems could be relevant to sub-category cs.CY (Computers and Society).
